This paper is about automatic quality estimation of natural language generation outputs using recurrent neural networks. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the arXiv sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as learning to rank and synthetic data, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also deals with pairwise rankings and correlation with human ratings, which could place it in the sub-categories of "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
